qas.question: How many Commonwealth nations are there?
What is the population of the Commonwealth?
How many Commonwealth nations still consider the British Queen their head of state?

context: Most former British colonies and protectorates are among the <a0_0>53<a0_0/> member states of the Commonwealth of Nations, a non-political, voluntary association of equal members, comprising a population of around <a1_0>2.2 billion<a1_0/> people. <a2_0>Sixteen<a2_0/> Commonwealth realms voluntarily continue to share the British monarch, Queen <a3_0>Elizabeth II<a3_0/>, as their head of state. These sixteen nations are distinct and equal legal entities – the United Kingdom, Australia, Canada, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, Antigua and Barbuda, The Bahamas, Barbados, Belize, Grenada, Jamaica, Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Lucia, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, Solomon Islands and Tuvalu.
